com.vector.cfg.util.scripting.groovy

Annotation Type VClassClosureParams


  • @Target(value=PARAMETER)
 @Retention(value=CLASS)
 @PublishedApi(value=CLASS_DEPENDENCY)
 @PublishedApiDomain(value=AUTOMATION_IF)
 @Documented
public @interface VClassClosureParams
    VClassClosureParams defines the parameters of the annotated Closure. The Class types specify the parameters of the closure. VClassClosureParams provides type information for the Groovy type system and IDE support.

    The usage of VClassClosureParams is especially good with the DelegatesTo annotation and the usage of ClosureCalls class.

    Details: the VClassClosureParams is converted during PublishedApi compile time to ClosureParams with SimpleType values. This shall ease the usage of the ClosureParams annotation that not string must encode the type information.

    (c) Copyright Vctr Informatik GmbH. All Rights Reserved.

    See Also:
    Closure, ClosureParams, SimpleType
